During a press briefing, White House Press Secretary Sean Spicer discussed various topics. He mentioned that President Trump held a listening session with the Attorney General and the Fraternal Order of Police to discuss law enforcement issues related to terrorism and inner-city violence. Spicer also mentioned that the President will sign an executive order on energy independence at the Environmental Protection Agency Headquarters. This order is aimed at ensuring clean air and water without sacrificing economic growth. Spicer also addressed the confirmation of Judge Neil Gorsuch to the Supreme Court, stating that the President hopes to find common ground with Senate Democrats. Additionally, Spicer discussed various economic developments, including Ford's $1.2 billion investment in three manufacturing facilities in Michigan and the rise in consumer confidence. Finally, Spicer addressed the controversy surrounding former Acting Attorney General Sally Yates, asserting that the White House did not prevent her from testifying before Congress.